sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K243024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This combination of parts use the benefits of an Strep-tag and is linked with a FluroescineA tag. The MiddleLinker (GlySerGlyGly)x2 produce a certain distance between the FluA tag and the protein domain Fok_a.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Freiburg Bioware09
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The linker length and the choice of the purification tag in combination with the anticalin tag allowed us several combination possiblities, which we had to prove to achieve the best combiantion.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Scar 25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is the scar produced by assembly using RFC 25.
If you are assembling a composite part using RFC 25, you can insert this part and specify blunt assembly to get the desired sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MiddleLink
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a linker, it can be used to connect two parts and add additional space between these parts. That can be necessary to avoid interactions between these parts. We used this part to connect our protein domains with our lipocalin domains, for our project the universal endonuclease.The sequence produced the aminoacids Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly-Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Freiburg Bioware09
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Oligos synthesized by sigma. Hybridized by PCR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K157004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Fluoresceine A -binding derivative of a Lipocalin (BBP, bilin binding protein from pieris brassicae), originally designed by Arne Skerra [see Ref. 1,2].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Freiburg 2008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Gene synthesis by GeneArt, optimized for expression in homo sapiens.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Between BioBrick 1.0 sites this part is flanked 5' by NgoMI(=NgoMIV) and 3' AgeI(=PinAI) to facilitate in frame cloning for protein fusions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Fok_a
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Protein domain (active) of the restriction endonuclease FokI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is used as the active domain of our universal restriction endonuclease. It cut double stranded DNA, when it fused with the inactive protein domain of our universal restriction endonuclease(BBa_K243001).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Freiburg Bioware09
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: extract coding region of Fok from the restriction-modification genes of the chromosomal DNA of Flavobacterium okeanokoites. Part synthesized by Mr.Gene
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Modifications of the vector (catalytic active heterodimer) -heterodimeric aminio acids
* switch Glutamate 490/310-312 to Lysin (GAA->AAA) * switch isoleucin 538/454-456 to Lysin (ATC->AAA)
